properties.Name: DunBradstreetCreditScoreClass
properties.Description:
The Dun & Bradstreet Credit Score Class is an assessment of the company's probable payment habits. 

Assesses the company's probable payment habits. A 1 to 5 Credit Score Class indicated the likelihood of an account becoming delinquent within the next 12 months. A 1 denotes low risk, 5 denotes high risk, and 0 denotes open bankruptcy and/or out of business at this location.

Commercial Credit Score Credit Score Percentile Credit Score Class Incidence of Delinquency 
1   536-670 91-100 1 2.5% 
2   493-535 71-90 2 4.8% 
3   423-492 31-70 3 12.9% 
4   376-422 11-30 4 24.2% 
5   101-375 1-10 5 58.8%
